gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 112, Kings 105
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Shai Gilgeous-Alexanders 40 points, seven rebounds and four assists, the Thunder defeated the Kings, 112-105. This is Gilgeous-Alexanders 6th 40+ point game of the season. Luguentz Dort notched 18 points, two rebounds, two assists and two steals for the Thunder in the victory, while DeAaron Fox (33 points, eight rebounds, six assists, seven 3PM) and Keon Ellis (career-high 26 points, eight 3PM) combined for 59 points for the Kings in the losing effort. Domantas Sabonis tallied eight points, 13 rebounds and five assists, ending his double-double streak at 61 consecutive games. The Thunder have won back-to-back games as they improve to 54-25 on the season, while the Kings fall to 45-34.
